==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dolphinfish
<hw>dolphinfish</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>either of two large slender food
and game fish (<spn>Coryphaena equisetis</spn> or <spn>Coryphaena
hippurus</spn>) of warm waters. They are highly esteemed as food fish,
especially in Hawaii, where they are usually referred to as
<altname>mahimahi</altname>. See also <er>dolphin{2}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dolphin, mahimahi.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

